<item>
            <title>[JDK-8309405] RISC-V: is_deopt may produce unaligned memory read</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8309405</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>After compressed opcodes were enabled by default, we  may have a 4-byte opcode located at 2-byte aligned address, but not 4-byte aligned address ( e.g. ending with 2/6/a/e in hex form)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This code then may produce misaligned read, and on some hardware (e.g. hifive) may result in misaligned load emulation thru m-mode&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;static bool is_deopt_at(address instr) {&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;assert(instr != nullptr, &amp;quot;&amp;quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;uint32_t value = *(uint32_t *) instr;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;// 0xc0201073 encodes CSRRW x0, instret, x0&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;return value == 0xc0201073;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;}&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
direct pointer dereference should be replaced with a proper method</description>
